<ul><li>"Survivor of '32 Syphilis Study Recalls a Diagnosis" (July 27, 1972), by
<a href="week5b.html">James
T. Wooten</a></li></ul>

<ul><li>"All in the Name of Science" (July 30, 1972), by <a href="week5c.html">Jane
E. Brody</a></li></ul>

<ul><li><a href="week5d.html">The Belmont Report</a>
(1979), by the National Commission for the Protection of Human Subjects
of Biomedical and Behavioral Research</li></ul>

<ul><li><a href="week5e.html">Final Report of the Tuskegee
Syphilis Study Legacy Committee</a> (1996)</li></ul>

<ul><li><a href="week5f.html">Presidential Apology</a>
(1997), to African-American participants in the "Tuskegee Study of Untreated
Syphilis in the Negro Male"</li></ul>
<ul>
  <li>
"U.S. Apologizes for Syphilis Tests in Guatemala" (October 1, 2010), by <a href="week5g.html">Donald G. McNeil, Jr.</a> with contributions from Elisabeth Malkin.</li>
</ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
 </table>   
